title: WATCH: Braxton Miller shows off a new receiving skill
text:
WATCH: Braxton Miller shows off a new receiving skill Ohio State quarterback-turned-receiver Braxton Miller made an amazing catch at Rutgers on Saturday night. Oct 24, 2015 at 9:46p ET 0Shares 
With so much focus on the two current Ohio State quarterbacks, maybe the former quarterback still on the roster was feeling overlooked. 
Consider that taken care of with Braxton Miller's amazing adjustment and juggling catch in the first half against Rutgers on Saturday night. 
The play went for 45 yards and gave Ohio State a first down at the Rutgers 18. 
Miller took a direct snap and ran 16 yards on the next play, setting up a 2-yard touchdown run by J.T. Barrett that gave the Buckeyes a 21-0 lead. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters. 0
